{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_26","type":"agent_message","text":"Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated job failed for `io.rest-assured:rest-assured-common:5.5.0`. Preserved work is available on the preserved branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2674-library-new-request-io.rest-assured-rest-assured-common-5.5.0-9ae00d66\n\nThe most likely failing stage was test generation for the new-library request. `stats/io.rest-assured/rest-assured-common/5.5.0/execution-metrics.json` shows 18 iterations with `generated_loc: 0`, no recorded test or metadata artifact, and no commit progress from `acb6dadc5e620a905cd36281b410d26f6bb4196e`. The generated test source still contains only the scaffold placeholder in `tests/src/io.rest-assured/rest-assured-common/5.5.0/src/test/java/io_rest_assured/rest_assured_common/Rest_assured_commonTest.java`, and the dynamic-access report stayed at 5/14 covered calls (35.71%), so automation did not converge on a valid library-specific test.\n\nFollow-up verification also exposed native-image/metadata issues. `logs/io.rest-assured:rest-assured-common:5.5.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-10T05-45-43-293813Z.log` shows 19 native test failures rooted in Groovy initialization (`InvokerHelper` / `GroovySystem`, starting from `AssertParameter.groovy:21`). `logs/io.rest-assured:rest-assured-common:5.5.0/native-test-verify/cycle-0-generateMetadata-2026-05-10T05-46-58-364374Z.log` failed because `native-image-agent` could not be loaded, and `logs/io.rest-assured:rest-assured-common:5.5.0/native-test-verify/cycle-0-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-10T05-47-01-800725Z.log` aborted because `TraceMetadataConditionPackages` was set to the invalid value `io.rest-assured`. `logs/io.rest-assured:rest-assured-common:5.5.0/metadata-fix/codex.log` then shows the remaining misses shifting to Groovy/JDK hierarchy types such as `java.io.Flushable` and `groovy.lang.Buildable`.\n\nInspect these logs first:\n- `logs/io.rest-assured:rest-assured-common:5.5.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-10T05-45-43-283695Z.log`\n- `logs/io.rest-assured:rest-assured-common:5.5.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-10T05-45-43-293813Z.log`\n- `logs/io.rest-assured:rest-assured-common:5.5.0/native-test-verify/cycle-0-generateMetadata-2026-05-10T05-46-58-364374Z.log`\n- `logs/io.rest-assured:rest-assured-common:5.5.0/native-test-verify/cycle-0-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-10T05-47-01-800725Z.log`\n- `logs/io.rest-assured:rest-assured-common:5.5.0/metadata-fix/codex.log`\n\nNext steps:\n1. Replace the scaffold test with a real, library-specific native test for `rest-assured-common` that exercises `AssertParameter` / `AssertionSupport` behavior and improves dynamic-access coverage.\n2. Re-run metadata tracing with a valid Java package prefix for `TraceMetadataConditionPackages` and a GraalVM installation that includes `native-image-agent`.\n3. If native tests still fail, use the Groovy initialization stack from the `gradle-test` and `metadata-fix/codex.log` outputs to add the missing reflection metadata for the required Groovy/JDK hierarchy types."}}
